<subSubSection box="[151,586,833,859]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,586,833,859]" box="[151,586,833,859]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,586,833,859]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,586,833,859]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Schott, 1893" authorityName="Schott" authorityYear="1893" box="[238,586,833,859]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,426,833,859]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Campylothorax</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schott" box="[432,586,833,859]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Schott, H. (1893) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Insektenfauna von Kameroon. I. Collembola. Bihang till Kongliga Svenska Fetenskaps-Akademien Handligar, 19, 1 - 28 + 7 plates." type="book chapter" year="1893">Schött, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="161" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,903,1936]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,903,928]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Adult specimens large (up to 
<quantity box="[610,700,903,928]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
). Body pigments forming distinct color patterns, specimens never totally white and rarely with diffused and uniform pigments covering all body. Heavily ciliate scales present, apically rounded or irregular. Dorsal head and trunk with reduced number of mac. Dorsal-anterior cephalic bothriotricha present. Antennae long, more than twice the total length of body. Eyes 8+8, lenses G and H reduced, sometimes hardly visible. Th. III enlarged and conspicuously humped, resulting in a bent body between Th. III and Abd. I (
<figureCitation box="[246,319,1084,1109]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1712,1735]" captionTargetBox="[269,1317,401,1691]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[269,1317,401,1691]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Paronellinae: 1, Salina sp., lateral view of mucro; 2, Campylothorax sabanus (Wray, 1953) modified of Mari Mutt (1987), distal antennal segments and color pattern omitted; 3, Lepidonella zeppelinii Soto-Adames &amp; Bellini, 2015, after original description; 4, manubrium of Paronella fusca Schött, 1893, after Mitra, 1992." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838042/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Th. II–Abd. V with ms and sens formula 10|10100 and 11|011–3, respectively. Abd. II to IV bothriotricha formula as 2/3/3 or 2/3/4 (secondary lateral bothriotricha-like chaetae sometimes present). Manubrium without spines; dens with one or two rows of spines and/or elongated ciliate spiniform mac; mucro elongate with 5 or rarely 4 or 6 teeth (adapted from 
<bibRefCitation author="Mitra" box="[749,985,1191,1216]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Mitra S. K. &amp; Dallai R. (1980) Studies of the genus Campylothorax Schott, 1893 (Collembola Entomobryidae Paronellinae) with the description of a new species from Zaire. Italian Journal of Zoology, 9, 273 - 321." type="journal article" year="1980">Mitra &amp; Dallai 1980</bibRefCitation>
, Cipola &amp; Oliveira 2016, 
<bibRefCitation author="Soto-Adames" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Soto-Adames, F. N. (2016) Chaetotaxy of first-instar Campylothorax sabanus (Wray), and description of three new Campylothorax species from Hispaniola (Collembola, Paronellidae). Journal of Natural History, 1 - 30." type="book chapter" year="2016">Soto-Adames 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="161" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,903,1936]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1585326940" country="Brazil" county="Remarks on Brazilian" location="Northeast Region of Brazil" municipality="Sao Francisco do Sul" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" specimenCount="3" stateProvince="Hamburg" typeStatus="holotype">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,548,1263,1288]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<collectingCounty box="[199,464,1263,1288]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Remarks on Brazilian</collectingCounty>
fauna.
</emphasis>
The species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schott" authorityYear="1893" box="[728,902,1263,1288]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[728,902,1263,1288]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Campylothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1079,1147,1263,1288]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Brazil</collectingCountry>
are: 
<taxonomicName authority="Mitra &amp; Dallai, 1980" authorityName="Mitra &amp; Dallai" authorityYear="1980" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cassagnaui">
<emphasis box="[1206,1366,1264,1288]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">C. cassagnaui</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mitra" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Mitra S. K. &amp; Dallai R. (1980) Studies of the genus Campylothorax Schott, 1893 (Collembola Entomobryidae Paronellinae) with the description of a new species from Zaire. Italian Journal of Zoology, 9, 273 - 321." type="journal article" year="1980">Mitra &amp; Dallai, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bellini &amp; Meneses, 2012" authorityName="Bellini &amp; Meneses" authorityYear="2012" box="[340,745,1300,1325]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mitrai">
<emphasis box="[340,444,1301,1324]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">C. mitrai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini" box="[453,745,1300,1325]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Bellini, B. C. &amp; Meneses, L. F. (2012) A new species of Campylothorax (Collembola: Entomobryoidea: Paronellidae) from the state of Alagoas, Brazil. Zoologia, 29 (5), 451 - 454." type="journal article" year="2012">Bellini &amp; Meneses, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cipola &amp; Oliveira, 2016" authorityName="Cipola &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2016" box="[758,1183,1300,1325]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagatus">
<emphasis box="[758,891,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">C. plagatus</emphasis>
Cipola &amp; Oliveira, 2016
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Borner, 1906" authorityName="Borner" authorityYear="1906" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schaefferi">
<emphasis box="[1197,1342,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">C. schaefferi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Borner" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Borner, C. (1906) Das system der Collembolen nebst Beschreibung neuer Collembolen des Hamburger Naturhistorischen Museums. Mitteilungen aus dem Naturhistorischen Museum in Hamburg, 23, 147 - 188." type="journal article" year="1906">Börner, 1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos, Cipola &amp; Bellini, 2016" authorityName="Santos, Cipola &amp; Bellini" authorityYear="2016" box="[268,787,1335,1360]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viruaensis">
<emphasis box="[268,418,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">C. viruaensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Santos" box="[429,787,1335,1360]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Santos, I. P. S., Cipola, N. G., Morais, J. W. &amp; Bellini, B. C. (2016) A new species of Campylothorax Schott (Collembola: Paronellidae: Paronellianae) from Northern Brazil. Zoologia, 33 (3), 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2016">Santos, Cipola &amp; Bellini, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(in: 
<bibRefCitation author="Santos" box="[846,1060,1335,1360]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Santos, I. P. S., Cipola, N. G., Morais, J. W. &amp; Bellini, B. C. (2016) A new species of Campylothorax Schott (Collembola: Paronellidae: Paronellianae) from Northern Brazil. Zoologia, 33 (3), 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2016">
Santos 
<emphasis box="[931,991,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Abrantes" box="[1074,1313,1335,1360]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Abrantes, E. A., Bellini, B. C., Bernardo, A. N., Fernandes, L. H., Mendonca, M. C., Oliveira, E. P., Queiroz, G. C., Sautter, K. D., Silveira, T. C. &amp; Zeppelini, D. (2012) Errata Corrigenda and update for the &quot; Synthesis of Brazilian Collembola: an update to the species list. &quot; ABRANTES et al. (2010) Zootaxa, 2388, 1 - 22. Zootaxa, 3168, 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="2012">
Abrantes 
<emphasis box="[1185,1244,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Bellini, B. C. &amp; Meneses, L. F. (2012) A new species of Campylothorax (Collembola: Entomobryoidea: Paronellidae) from the state of Alagoas, Brazil. Zoologia, 29 (5), 451 - 454." type="journal article" year="2012">Bellini &amp; Meneses 2012</bibRefCitation>
, Cipola &amp; Oliveira 2016,). The 
<typeStatus box="[685,733,1373,1397]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">type</typeStatus>
locality of the presumably widely distributed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borner" authorityYear="1906" box="[1263,1408,1372,1397]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schaefferi">
<emphasis box="[1263,1408,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">C. schaefferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unknown. Börner’s description was based on specimens harvested from orchids grown in 
<collectingCountry box="[1182,1287,1408,1432]" name="Germany" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Germany</collectingCountry>
, in 
<collectingRegion box="[1331,1436,1407,1432]" country="Germany" name="Hamburg" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Hamburg</collectingRegion>
Museum (University of 
<collectingRegion box="[422,532,1444,1469]" country="Germany" name="Hamburg" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Hamburg</collectingRegion>
), collected from “São Francisco, 
<collectingCountry box="[908,982,1444,1469]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Brazil</collectingCountry>
”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mitra" box="[1003,1253,1444,1469]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Mitra S. K. &amp; Dallai R. (1980) Studies of the genus Campylothorax Schott, 1893 (Collembola Entomobryidae Paronellinae) with the description of a new species from Zaire. Italian Journal of Zoology, 9, 273 - 321." type="journal article" year="1980">Mitra &amp; Dallai (1980)</bibRefCitation>
provided a map indicating the 
<typeStatus box="[317,365,1480,1504]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">type</typeStatus>
locality as 
<collectingMunicipality box="[504,750,1479,1504]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">São Francisco do Sul</collectingMunicipality>
municipality, Santa Catarina State, 
<collectingCountry box="[1168,1240,1479,1504]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. But the original description does not provide such data. In a Brazilian geographical context “São Francisco” can be the largest river in 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:6F20573334213A08CC8AFC824700FCED:E256B0FE34213A08CCABF9CC47DEFD55" box="[182,492,1551,1576]" country="Brazil" county="Remarks on Brazilian" municipality="Sao Francisco do Sul" name="Northeast Region of Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" stateProvince="Hamburg">Northeast Region of Brazil</location>
or a municipality name (and there are at least five Brazilian municipalities in far apart states with the same name). Because of this and in the absence of the 
<typeStatus box="[1038,1086,1589,1613]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">type</typeStatus>
material (destroyed according curators of University of 
<collectingRegion box="[432,540,1623,1648]" country="Germany" name="Hamburg" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Hamburg</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[551,660,1624,1648]" name="Germany" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Germany</collectingCountry>
), the identity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borner" authorityYear="1906" box="[840,983,1623,1648]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schaefferi">
<emphasis box="[840,983,1623,1648]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">C. schaefferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be further investigated. Also, the condition of 4 mucronal teeth reported to the species in 
<bibRefCitation author="Mitra" box="[792,1045,1660,1685]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Mitra S. K. &amp; Dallai R. (1980) Studies of the genus Campylothorax Schott, 1893 (Collembola Entomobryidae Paronellinae) with the description of a new species from Zaire. Italian Journal of Zoology, 9, 273 - 321." type="journal article" year="1980">Mitra &amp; Dallai (1980)</bibRefCitation>
maybe possibly because the basal tooth could be very small in some specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schott" authorityYear="1893" box="[721,895,1695,1720]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[721,895,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Campylothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as we observed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bellini &amp; Meneses" authorityYear="2012" box="[1132,1236,1696,1720]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mitrai">
<emphasis box="[1132,1236,1696,1720]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">C. mitrai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or even due the analysis of abnormal specimens.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,903,1936]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
The recent descriptions of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cipola &amp; Oliveira" authorityYear="2016" box="[502,633,1767,1792]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagatus">
<emphasis box="[502,633,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">C. plagatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos, Cipola &amp; Bellini" authorityYear="2016" box="[647,796,1768,1792]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viruaensis">
<emphasis box="[647,796,1768,1792]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">C. viruaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and now the redescription of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bellini &amp; Meneses" authorityYear="2012" box="[1138,1241,1768,1792]" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mitrai">
<emphasis box="[1138,1241,1768,1792]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">C. mitrai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may point out to other two diagnostic features within the genus, or at least to the Neotropical species: absence of the pretarsal chaetae and of the smooth chaeta opposite to the tenent hair on the hind unguiculus, commonly found in practically all other taxa of Entomobryoidea. This late feature was already reported by 
<bibRefCitation box="[1046,1264,1876,1901]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Mari Mutt, J. (1987 a) Puerto Rican species of Paronellidae (Insecta: Collembola). Caribbean Journal of Science, 23, 400 - 416." type="journal article">Mari Mutt (1987a)</bibRefCitation>
to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wray, 1953" authorityName="Wray" authorityYear="1953" class="Entognatha" family="Paronellidae" genus="Campylothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabanus">
<emphasis box="[1308,1436,1876,1901]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">C. sabanus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wray" box="[158,293,1911,1936]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" refString="Wray, D. L. (1953) New Collembola from Puerto Rico. The Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico, 37 (2), 140 - 150." type="journal article" year="1953">Wray, 1953</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
